mixed conifer and well‐drained spruce forests were less resilient. However, simulation modeling suggests increased fire activity may result in large changes in forest age structure and composition, despite the feedbacks between vegetation‐fire likely to occur with increased fire activity.{\textless}/p{\textgreater} {\textless}p{\textgreater}This article is protected by copyright. All rights reserved.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
