d were regarded. Climate change added another 23–31{\%} increase, while changes in forest area accounted for an additional increase of 2–40{\%}. Our results highlight potential future pathways of forest resource development resulting from different scenarios of wood demand, land use and climate changes, and stress the importance of resource utilization in the European forest carbon balance.},
